iter88: genphy_soft_reset on user port enable (EN751221 PHYs)

Per Caleb DeLisle openwrt-devel "Debugging EcoNet's MT7530 PHYs"
mail-archive thread (msg67880-67906): the EN751221 GE PHYs need a
BMCR=0x9200 (RESET|ANRESTART) to clear bad AN state and start RX
properly; BMCR=0x1240 (ANENABLE|ANRESTART) alone leaves RX dead.

Apply genphy_soft_reset on port enable for both ID_EN751221 (on-die
MMIO switch) and ID_EN751221_EXT (MCM external switch). genphy_soft_reset
writes BMCR_RESET which is exactly what's needed.

--- a/gsw/mt7530.c
+++ b/gsw/mt7530.c
@@ -1995,6 +1995,11 @@ mt7530_port_enable(struct dsa_switch *ds, int port,
 	int upstream_pt = dsa_switch_upstream_port(ds);
 	struct dsa_port *dp = dsa_to_port(ds, port);
 	struct mt7530_priv *priv = ds->priv;
+
+	/* iter88: clear bad AN state on EN751221 PHYs (Caleb WIP). */
+	if ((priv->id == ID_EN751221 || priv->id == ID_EN751221_EXT) && phy)
+		genphy_soft_reset(phy);
+	dev_warn(priv->dev, "ITER88: port_enable port=%d phy=%p\n", port, phy);
 
 	/* Allow the user port gets connected to the cpu port and also
 	 * restore the port matrix if the port is the member of a certain
